# Steam session stack (Phase 3) — all from Arch Linux ARM (aarch64), NOT holo.
# gamescope is in ALARM extra (3.16.24, newer than holo's 3.16.17) and built against ALARM's
# mesa, so there's no ABI risk and no need for the holo repo / its core+extra name collision.
# mesa is already in base.list (ALARM).
#
# The native ARM Steam CLIENT is not a pacman package — it's bootstrapped at first launch
# (steamrtarm64), handled by the session launcher (pocknix-steam). Not listed here.

# gamescope is NOT here: vanilla gamescope can't drive the RP6's rotated msm panel, so we
# build a ROCKNIX-patched gamescope (packages/gamescope, epoch=1) and install it from the
# local [pocknix] repo via install_local_packages in build-image.sh. (If it were listed here
# too, ALARM's would install first and `--needed` would skip ours.)
xorg-xwayland      # required by gamescope's --xwayland-count (also a gamescope dep)
# mangohud         # perf overlay — re-enable once aarch64 availability in ALARM is confirmed
